cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with constructing sparse spanners for a set of points in Euclidean space, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of primitive recursive hierarchy and logarithmic functions suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The optimization of the time complexity also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization and control (cs.SI).
